	   <tr><td colspan=2>I (52 bard) took this guy down a few days ago.. first I tried him with a 52 druid 52 warrior and 53 wizard, but he ended up killing us all when he was at 25% HP (wizard was chain IC'ing him for whatever reason and kept getting summoned, and my fear wouldn't stick for more than 1-2 seconds at a time). Anyway, after we got our rez, we sent out the call over guildchat, and within 20 mins or so had two full groups in skyfire, after which he went down very easily. We didnt even bother fearkiting him... went down fairly fast although he was harder than Nezekezena, who was also lvl 51 when we killed her.<br><br>Some general info on Edrig: he's lvl 51, summons, is immune to fire like all chromos, casts the same DoT chromos do, casts the same dispel they do (except his is an AoE dispel), hits for 150ish max. Pulling him can be annoying because he wanders through that field of dragon bones in skyfire that's always full of mobs... was even harder this time because there was a red at 52 mob named 'ancient wyvern' on almost the same pathing he was.<br><br>Very happy I didn't have to camp this guy, and am now the proud owner of page 25 of my symphony.<br><br>- Masakari Yakikorosu<br>Bard of 52 Songs<br>-=Improbus Odium=-<br>MT<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
